# 3. I & W Assessment of the Three Risks

The I & W-derived probabilities closely reconcile with the qualitative register scores:

| Risk | Quantitative Probability | Qualitative Probability |
|--------|--------|--------|
| R1 | 0.65 | 0.70 |
| R2 | 0.47 | 0.50 |
| R3 | 0.62 | 0.70 |

This validates the earlier qualitative judgment while adding a defensible quantitative basis.

Real-world benchmark parameters include:

- UPS ORION route optimization savings of approximately **US$300–400 million annually**
- Average global data breach cost of **US$4.44 million**
- Average U.S. data breach cost of **US$10.22 million**
- Last-mile delivery representing approximately **53% of total shipping costs**

